description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for a Practice Nurse interested in joining a friendly, local GP surgery.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Opportunities available at 2 practices in South East London&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knights Hill Surgery, West Norwood, London SE27 0DF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Penrose Surgery, Walworth, London SE17 3DW&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours&lt;/strong&gt;: Full Time or Part-Time, weekdays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: £36 – 44,000 FT depending on experience. Overtime paid if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;Private medical insurance, sick pay, opportunity for funded professional development, paid professional indemnity, cycle scheme, regular activities and resilience support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working with our clinical teams to deliver the highest quality primary care service to our patients. More specifically, our Practice Nurses are responsible for the normal clinical nursing duties and nursing management / administrative work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cervical screening&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contraception, sexual health and family planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Child immunisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seasonal and adult vaccinations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel immunisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long term condition management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wound care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support of health care assistants and phlebotomists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right candidate will demonstrate strong interpersonal and communication skills for dealing with our varied patient population, and be able to work in a close-knit team of both clinicians and non-clinicians. Strong clinical knowledge and good analytical skills are important to ensure successful consultations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Minimum requirements: Registered Nurse with a minimum of 1 year working in GP Primary Care setting is required. Previous experience working with EMIS preferred but not required. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a small group of close-knit surgeries in South East London on a mission to give our patients the best healthcare in London. We use a multidisciplinary approach – bringing together GPs, Nurses, HCAs, Pharmacists, Paramedics and Mental Health Nurses to deliver an efficient and effective service with strong outcomes for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With high levels of patient satisfaction and low waiting times, we’ve been able to grow to almost 50,000 patients and we continue to grow at a rapid pace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We serve our patients across 7 CQC ‘Good’ rated sites in Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham, with each site having its own dedicated multidisciplinary team. You’ll join one of these site-based teams but you’ll be part of the larger Penrose Health family as well!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of Team Penrose, you will be covered by our Vitality Private Health Insurance, you’ll have the choice of a NOW or NHS pension and you’ll benefit from a comprehensive sick pay scheme after your first year with us. We also pay your professional indemnity and you’ll have the opportunity for funded professional development in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On top of the employment benefits, this year we have seen a month dedicated to appreciating our team members, offered art on line classes, enjoyed ice cream from a visiting ice cream van, enjoyed surprise gifts, thank you self-care bags, fresh fruit deliveries, hosted a group-wide bake-off and this month we&#39;ll be having some Halloween fun! These are just some (but not all) of the things we do to make this a great place to work! Underneath all of this, you will also find a core strength and camaraderie that exists in each of our surgery teams and across the group – we really are a family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our team are enthusiastic, friendly and we want to make a real difference to our patients – come and be a part of the team!&lt;/p&gt;
